# Repository notes (displayed after build)
NOTES="# Amstrad Audio Issue

When Amstrad CPC audio is accompanied by a constent humming note, opening ZEsarUX Settings > Audio and set the system to use only one AY chip.

Some CPC users might need to set the audio driver from its default value to SDL.

# Amstrad Games

Games can be downloaded from https://amstradmuseum.emu-france.info/
Direct link to the disk files: https://amstradmuseum.emu-france.info/Fichiers/DSK/

Are you using Linux? Download all the software from Amstrad Museum by putting this line into a terminal:

mkdir "~/CPC Games"; cd "~/CPC Games"; wget -r -np -nH --cut-dirs=1 -A "*" "https://amstradmuseum.emu-france.info/Fichiers/DSK/"

Software will download into 'CPC Games' under your home directory. Move them to wherever you want to store them.

# Spectrum Software

ZEsarUX has a bult in software browser to find Spectrum software and download it to your home directory at (on Linux) ~/.zesarux/Games
NB '~/' represents your home directory e.g $HOME

Use the Software Browser by opening the ZEsarUX menu and clicking Network > ZX81 Browser or Network > Software Browser.

# Software for other systems

Try archive.org

You will need to search the software archive for the games system you wish to use.

The 'Non merged' MAME software should work in ZEsarUX too."

